Subject: A Truth Universally Acknowledged: Swift Design Patterns As Jane Austen Heroes
Description: Have you ever looked at your code and realized that a certain design pattern was charging in like a romantic hero, sweeping away the confusion and bringing order to chaos? Or perhaps you've encountered a pattern that you utterly hated...until it's virtues slowly grew on you as you realized that the alternative was a complete disaster? Let's imagine Ada Lovelace reading Jane Austen, and compare some of my favorite design patterns with some of my favorite Jane Austen heroes (neither knowledge of Swift nor Jane Austen are required).  Speakers include:Anne Cahalan - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
